Condition : 4 - No development above ground level shall take place until samples of all materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. 
The samples/details shall include: 
a)	Brickwork/stonework;
b)	Cladding materials/render;
c)	Tiles/roof covering;
d)	Window treatments (including sections/reveals); and 
e)	Any other materials/details/ fittings to be used, with sections and on-site samples where appropriate.

Condition : 7 - Prior to the commencement of the development hereby approved, details of a Construction Logistics Plan (CLP) must been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The CLP shall cover as a minimum:  
- a site plan; 
- a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway to be agreed with the Council; 
- provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors; 
- provision for loading and unloading of plant and materials within the site; 
- provision for the storage of plant and materials used in constructing the development ; 
- the erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative displays and facilities for public viewing, where appropriate;  
- wheel washing facilities at the site exit; 
- measures to control the emission of dust and dirt during construction;  
- a scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works; 
- appropriate vehicle routes to and from the site; 
- measures to ensure the safety of all user of the public highway especially in the vicinity of the site; 
- use of operators committed to best practice, demonstrated by membership of TfL's Freight Operator Recognition Scheme (FORS), or similar; and
- measures to promote sustainable travel to work. All construction works shall be managed in accordance with the approved CMP.
